'''Open source culture''' is the creative practice of appropriation and free sharing of found and created content. Examples include [[collage]], [[found footage]] film, [[music]], and [[appropriation art]]. Open source culture is one in which [[fixation]]s, works entitled to copyright protection, are made generally available. Participants in the culture can modify those products and redistribute them back into the community or other organizations.
